This paper is about a clustering method using a feed-forward neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, it deals with non-linear feed-forward neural networks and their application to clustering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of abstracted features and the comparison of results using purity, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
